WEBVTT

00:06.658 --> 00:09.009
[no audio]

00:16.755 --> 00:19.149
[bright music]

00:26.722 --> 00:29.159
[bright music]

00:36.732 --> 00:39.169
[bright music]

00:43.956 --> 00:45.915
[dramatic music]
[hooves clopping]

00:46.089 --> 00:46.916
[projector clacking]

00:47.090 --> 00:49.397
[whip cracks]

00:53.053 --> 00:55.446
[gentle music]

01:03.019 --> 01:06.066
[gentle music continues]

01:12.463 --> 01:14.596
[gentle music continues]

01:14.770 --> 01:17.207
[engine revving]

01:19.253 --> 01:22.299
- [sighs] I told you to get
those signs out of the back,

01:22.473 --> 01:24.606
clean those tools out
of the truck, did I not?

01:24.780 --> 01:25.302
- Yes, sir.

01:28.566 --> 01:30.742
- Everybody already knows
I work two jobs, but,

01:32.135 --> 01:33.571
my Lord, they
shouldn't have to look

01:33.745 --> 01:35.138
at a rolling billboard
in the parking lot.

01:36.531 --> 01:37.749
- I'm sorry, Daddy. I forgot.

01:41.492 --> 01:44.539
- Sister Abernathie, she's,
uh, she's at her wit's end.

01:48.369 --> 01:50.632
Your behavior has been off.

01:52.590 --> 01:54.288
And you better do right
in that classroom today,

01:54.462 --> 01:56.116
or I'll ground you for another
week, you understand me?

01:56.290 --> 01:56.942
- Yes, sir.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.336
- Look, I was a
preacher's kid, too.

02:00.859 --> 02:02.078
But you got to do right, son,

02:04.167 --> 02:05.647
'cause if you don't,

02:07.953 --> 02:09.129
I'ma have to talk to my friend,

02:11.087 --> 02:12.349
Gary, the Goose.

02:13.176 --> 02:14.482
Oh, man, he's hungry.

02:14.656 --> 02:15.831
- Daddy, no! Please, no!
- He's so hungry.

02:16.005 --> 02:16.701
- No, please! No!
- He's hungry!

02:16.875 --> 02:18.790
[both laughing]

02:18.964 --> 02:22.142
[gentle music continues]

02:28.322 --> 02:31.586
[gentle music continues]

02:33.501 --> 02:36.808
- [Samuel] Daddy, who
parked in your spot?

02:42.858 --> 02:44.207
- Go on in, son.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.303
- And things like cussing
will get you there.

02:54.913 --> 02:59.309
The word of God says, "Let
your conversation be holy."

03:00.658 --> 03:03.270
The word says, "Be ye holy

03:03.444 --> 03:05.228
as I am holy."

03:05.402 --> 03:07.709
[upbeat music]

03:08.884 --> 03:09.624
What, Samuel?

03:11.495 --> 03:13.105
- I know you said cussing
will get you in,

03:13.280 --> 03:15.978
but what if you, like,
just tried it once,

03:16.152 --> 03:17.545
and you didn't really mean it?

03:17.719 --> 03:19.199
What if Jesus came
back right then?

03:20.461 --> 03:21.897
- Come here.

03:22.071 --> 03:25.248
[upbeat music continues]

03:26.728 --> 03:27.337
Come right here.

03:28.686 --> 03:29.905
Then, boy,

03:30.079 --> 03:31.950
you'd bust wide open.

03:32.124 --> 03:32.821
[congregation applauding]

03:32.995 --> 03:35.432
[bright music]

03:36.999 --> 03:38.479
- Ma'am.

03:38.653 --> 03:41.046
- [sighs] What, Samuel?

03:41.221 --> 03:42.657
- Can I go to the bathroom?

03:45.616 --> 03:46.400
- Hurry back.

03:49.838 --> 03:51.796
- The Lord looks on the heart.

03:51.970 --> 03:54.538
Now, the GCO guidebook
says no swimming,

03:56.410 --> 04:00.327
no makeup, no worldly music,
no going to the picture show.

04:00.501 --> 04:01.893
- That's right.
- Yes.

04:02.067 --> 04:03.547
- And there's probably
a million people

04:03.721 --> 04:06.594
in this organization who
follow those rules to tee.

04:06.768 --> 04:08.204
- I do, Pastor.

04:08.378 --> 04:10.162
- I know you do,
Zachary. I know you do.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.556
[congregation chuckling]

04:12.730 --> 04:13.905
But what about those people

04:15.472 --> 04:19.389
that are following those
rules on the outside,

04:19.563 --> 04:21.870
but they're doing something
different on the inside?

04:23.698 --> 04:27.876
Right, someone who wouldn't
dare touch a bottle of whiskey,

04:29.747 --> 04:33.055
and yet they walk around
drunk on their own pride.

04:33.229 --> 04:34.839
[congregation muttering]

04:35.013 --> 04:35.927
God looks on the heart.

04:37.668 --> 04:39.627
Someone who wouldn't even think

04:39.801 --> 04:41.933
about lighting up
a single cigarette,

04:45.459 --> 04:48.853
but their heart is
burnt up with jealousy.

04:49.027 --> 04:51.552
[congregation muttering]

04:51.726 --> 04:52.509
See, because God,

04:54.729 --> 04:56.034
he knows how to spot a fake.

04:57.819 --> 05:01.649
And if we don't tell him
every single day how we fail,

05:01.823 --> 05:02.693
and we need his help,

05:04.478 --> 05:07.132
then our own hearts
will go astray.

05:07.307 --> 05:08.830
- Oh yes.
- Amen.

05:09.004 --> 05:12.137
- 'Cause where religion
fails and where people fail,

05:13.661 --> 05:15.706
God will never, and
I mean never fail.

05:17.186 --> 05:18.361
Hallelujah.

05:18.535 --> 05:19.231
- Amen!
[congregation applauding]

05:19.406 --> 05:21.321
[upbeat music]

05:24.715 --> 05:27.239
♪ Are you ready to go ♪

05:27.414 --> 05:29.851
♪ Have you talked to the Lord ♪

05:30.025 --> 05:32.332
♪ Is there peace in your heart ♪

05:32.506 --> 05:36.858
♪ Has your faith been restored ♪

05:37.032 --> 05:39.077
♪ Glory to God ♪

05:39.251 --> 05:43.473
♪ I'll not be ashamed ♪

05:43.647 --> 05:45.823
♪ Jesus, my Jesus ♪

05:45.997 --> 05:48.870
♪ He knows my name ♪

05:49.044 --> 05:52.221
[upbeat music continues]

05:55.050 --> 05:56.878
♪ Getting hot ♪

05:57.052 --> 05:59.054
♪ Real hot ♪

05:59.228 --> 06:03.624
♪ And I'ma burning, burning,
burning, burning up ♪

06:03.798 --> 06:06.670
- Shh! Are you trying
to get us in trouble?

06:06.844 --> 06:08.672
You know I can't listen
to that kinda music.

06:08.846 --> 06:10.413
- That's stupid!

06:10.587 --> 06:11.675
- It's just the way it is.

06:11.849 --> 06:13.547
- That white boy got soul.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.026
You should go and
see "Jailhouse Rock"

06:15.200 --> 06:16.680
with me and my
grandma this Saturday.

06:16.854 --> 06:19.161
You just hear him sing one time.

06:19.335 --> 06:20.902
See what all the fuss is about.

06:21.076 --> 06:22.773
- I've heard him sing.

06:22.947 --> 06:25.733
- Man, you ain't never heard
The King, preacher boy.

06:25.907 --> 06:28.213
- Barry, you get on my nerves.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.389
- Let's hear it.

06:37.005 --> 06:38.920
♪ It's getting hot ♪

06:39.094 --> 06:40.922
♪ Real hot ♪

06:41.096 --> 06:45.709
♪ And I'ma burning, burning,
burning, burning up ♪

06:45.883 --> 06:48.277
[upbeat music]

06:53.108 --> 06:54.283
- You sinner!

06:54.457 --> 06:58.461
[Samuel laughs]
[engine revving]

06:58.635 --> 07:01.899
- Hey, boys, go play
out in the back.

07:02.073 --> 07:03.161
- [Barry] Come on.
Let's go hustle.

07:03.335 --> 07:04.336
- [Samuel] All right.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.252
[engine rumbling]

07:13.650 --> 07:16.958
[Joe clears throat]

07:17.132 --> 07:18.829
- Just driving by?

07:19.003 --> 07:19.787
- Joe.

07:23.181 --> 07:25.227
That's quite a little show
you put on there this morning.

07:25.401 --> 07:26.881
- It's our church
state overseer.

07:27.055 --> 07:28.360
He tells everybody what to do.

07:28.535 --> 07:30.580
- [Joe] What do you need?

07:30.754 --> 07:33.365
- God's Church Organization
is growing by the hour.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.019
Lord's returning any day.

07:35.193 --> 07:37.239
We just need to make sure
that all of our pastors

07:37.413 --> 07:39.981
are preaching what they
ought to be preaching.

07:41.504 --> 07:42.157
- I haven't gotten
any complaints.

07:42.331 --> 07:43.680
- Mm.

07:43.854 --> 07:44.594
I have.

07:46.727 --> 07:48.685
Brother Wilburn let his
whole family go swimming.

07:49.904 --> 07:51.993
Mixed bathing encourages lust.

07:53.647 --> 07:57.041
Well, God's Church,
we show the way.

07:57.215 --> 07:58.173
- We can't just throw
a rule book at 'em

07:58.347 --> 07:59.522
and tell 'em to change.

08:00.697 --> 08:02.133
See,

08:02.307 --> 08:03.831
you and I, um, we're different.

08:05.310 --> 08:07.138
- Like Cain and Abel.

08:07.312 --> 08:08.879
- You're a professional.

08:09.053 --> 08:13.318
I'm just a boy that God
found out in a cotton field.

08:13.493 --> 08:14.450
When I was 14,

08:15.930 --> 08:18.280
your daddy asked me to
come and tell my story.

08:18.454 --> 08:19.411
- Yeah.

08:19.586 --> 08:20.848
Small town nothing.

08:22.240 --> 08:25.374
- Maybe, but I got ambition.

08:25.548 --> 08:28.203
Raise my son. Lead my people.

08:28.377 --> 08:29.160
- Your people?

08:30.335 --> 08:31.511
They're my people.

08:33.077 --> 08:34.818
My daddy ain't gonna live
forever. Remember that.

08:36.211 --> 08:37.647
- None of us do.

08:37.821 --> 08:40.520
[brooding music]

08:45.263 --> 08:46.743
- We'll see who's
smiling in the end.

08:49.137 --> 08:51.879
[engine starting]

08:53.445 --> 08:56.448
[brooding music continues]

08:56.623 --> 08:57.711
- Watch out for that bush!

08:58.799 --> 08:59.974
[brakes screech]

09:00.148 --> 09:00.888
You found it.

09:03.281 --> 09:05.588
[gentle music]

09:05.762 --> 09:08.330
- Someday I'll
start my own church

09:09.766 --> 09:11.202
and be a preacher like my daddy.

09:13.640 --> 09:16.556
[cutlery clacking]

09:21.952 --> 09:23.345
- Good Lord, ain't you
gonna ask about the present

09:23.519 --> 09:25.216
sitting right here on the table?

09:25.390 --> 09:25.956
- It's a present?

09:26.914 --> 09:27.654
For me?

09:29.307 --> 09:30.004
- Ain't my birthday.

09:31.832 --> 09:34.530
[paper rustling]

09:40.188 --> 09:42.712
[clock ticking]

09:43.800 --> 09:44.584
It's time.

09:51.329 --> 09:53.810
- Daddy, I've been
thinking a lot.

09:55.420 --> 09:56.770
I think I know why Momma died

09:56.944 --> 09:57.640
with my little
brother in her belly.

09:57.814 --> 09:58.598
- Hey.

10:00.121 --> 10:01.992
Remember, we don't question
Lord in those matters.

10:03.211 --> 10:03.951
You know that.

10:05.474 --> 10:08.390
- Daddy, I cussed a few times.

10:08.564 --> 10:09.304
On purpose.

10:09.478 --> 10:10.131
- Samuel, stop.

10:12.002 --> 10:12.786
- It's my fault.

10:15.919 --> 10:16.659
- Samuel.

10:18.269 --> 10:19.183
Samuel, look at me.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.273
Now, what you said right
there, that's not true.

10:23.927 --> 10:25.363
Your mother had
complications with the baby.

10:27.104 --> 10:29.629
- But Sister Abernathie
said I was going to

10:29.803 --> 10:31.152
because I cussed.

10:31.326 --> 10:32.675
- Well, you know what?

10:32.849 --> 10:33.937
I don't think Sister
Abernathie knows

10:34.111 --> 10:35.547
what she's
talking about.

10:35.722 --> 10:37.985
Oh! I just said it too, huh?

10:38.159 --> 10:40.552
[bright music]

10:40.727 --> 10:42.816
I'm gonna have to give
her a little talking to.

10:45.209 --> 10:47.908
Hey, you remember what we
used to say about God's love?

10:48.082 --> 10:50.432
Think about the
deepest, highest,

10:50.606 --> 10:54.044
strongest, and widest
thing there could ever be.

10:54.218 --> 10:56.046
That's God's love for
you and me. Yes, sir.

10:57.352 --> 11:00.529
[bright music continues]

11:02.400 --> 11:04.881
I want you to head over to
that closet. Open it up.

11:07.144 --> 11:08.276
Before your food gets cold.

11:16.980 --> 11:19.461
[gentle music]

11:25.946 --> 11:28.949
[gentle music continues]

11:29.123 --> 11:30.690
I traded your mother's
mandolin for it.

11:32.517 --> 11:33.475
It's yours, son.

11:35.129 --> 11:38.001
[gentle music continues]

11:38.175 --> 11:40.221
- I thought the GCO said
electric instruments

11:40.395 --> 11:41.222
are of the devil?

11:43.485 --> 11:46.923
- Well, rock and roll don't
sound too good on an acoustic.

11:49.534 --> 11:51.972
See? Your dad pays attention.

11:52.146 --> 11:55.366
[bright music]

11:55.540 --> 11:56.150
You got a gift, son.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.414
It's in your blood.

11:59.588 --> 12:01.938
[upbeat music]

12:07.161 --> 12:09.598
[upbeat music continues]

12:09.772 --> 12:12.296
♪ God is never busy ♪

12:12.470 --> 12:14.864
♪ He's always home ♪

12:15.038 --> 12:19.956
♪ Dial up your prayer
on Heaven's telephone ♪

12:20.827 --> 12:22.393
♪ If you need an answer ♪

12:22.567 --> 12:25.135
♪ When you feel at home ♪

12:25.309 --> 12:29.966
♪ Dial your prayers on
Heaven's telephone ♪

12:31.141 --> 12:32.403
♪ Say you got a bad connection ♪

12:32.577 --> 12:35.145
♪ No one understands ♪

12:35.319 --> 12:39.976
♪ I suggest an installation
straight to Gloryland ♪

12:41.717 --> 12:45.547
♪ Jesus will connect you
directly to his throne ♪

12:47.157 --> 12:50.813
♪ Dial your prayers on
Heaven's telephone ♪

12:52.075 --> 12:55.775
♪ Dial your prayers
on Heaven's ♪

12:56.645 --> 12:58.821
♪ Telephone ♪

13:00.214 --> 13:02.869
[audience cheering]

13:09.614 --> 13:11.355
- Give the Lord a praise!

13:11.529 --> 13:14.619
[audience cheering continues]

13:14.794 --> 13:15.620
Hallelujah.

13:16.926 --> 13:19.711
Glory be to God.
Glory, glory, glory.

13:19.886 --> 13:21.409
- Yes!
- Amen!

13:21.583 --> 13:23.628
- Y'all can be seated,
[chuckles] if you can.

13:26.457 --> 13:30.374
Now, if you don't feel the
Holy Ghost's power right now,

13:30.548 --> 13:32.246
then your wood

13:32.420 --> 13:33.508
is wet.

13:33.682 --> 13:36.641
[audience cheering]

13:38.078 --> 13:38.687
- [Audience Member]
Yeah! Hallelujah!

13:38.861 --> 13:39.644
- And we

13:40.907 --> 13:42.822
are going to win the world!

13:42.996 --> 13:46.390
[audience cheering]
And it makes me wanna dance!

13:46.564 --> 13:49.002
[upbeat music]

13:56.052 --> 13:59.273
[upbeat music continues]

14:03.146 --> 14:07.020
You all know Brother Joe
Allen over at GCO Sayre.

14:08.108 --> 14:09.109
He's a good man.

14:09.283 --> 14:10.675
- Yeah.
- Yes, sir.

14:10.850 --> 14:13.374
- Now, his son is
here today, Samuel.

14:13.548 --> 14:15.855
He's going to come up
and sing a song for us.

14:17.117 --> 14:18.553
Give the Lord a
praise in welcome.

14:18.727 --> 14:21.730
[audience cheering]

14:27.867 --> 14:31.914
[audience cheering continues]

14:32.088 --> 14:34.917
- I wanna marry him someday.

14:35.091 --> 14:36.614
- But Julie,

14:36.788 --> 14:37.964
I thought you said you were
gonna marry Jody Barnes?

14:40.488 --> 14:43.012
- Well, either him or Samuel.

14:43.186 --> 14:44.535
- I'm gonna sing a song called

14:44.709 --> 14:46.320
"I Hold a Clear
Title to a Mansion."

14:47.582 --> 14:48.626
My momma used to love it.

14:50.585 --> 14:53.066
[upbeat music]

14:58.767 --> 15:01.074
[upbeat music continues]

15:01.248 --> 15:06.166
♪ I've heard people
talk about Heaven ♪

15:07.210 --> 15:11.736
♪ Describing its
beauty so rare ♪

15:13.260 --> 15:16.872
♪ So I one day
purchased the title ♪

15:18.134 --> 15:22.138
♪ To a mansion in
that land so fair ♪

15:23.792 --> 15:27.883
♪ I hold a clear
title to a mansion ♪

15:29.189 --> 15:33.149
♪ That Jesus has
gone to prepare ♪

15:34.368 --> 15:36.936
♪ Fires cannot touch it ♪

15:37.110 --> 15:41.897
♪ Floods cannot harm it ♪

15:42.071 --> 15:46.989
♪ And it never will
need no repair ♪

15:47.816 --> 15:51.646
♪ Never will need ♪

15:51.820 --> 15:53.953
♪ Repair ♪

15:54.954 --> 15:57.957
[audience cheering]

16:02.831 --> 16:05.442
[audience cheering continues]

16:05.616 --> 16:06.530
- Thank you.

16:09.664 --> 16:11.013
- All right, now
let us remember,

16:11.187 --> 16:12.580
we do not clap for the man.

16:14.147 --> 16:18.281
We only clap for the Lord. Amen.

16:18.455 --> 16:19.195
Amen.

16:20.718 --> 16:22.372
All right, let's go
ahead and get the rest

16:22.546 --> 16:25.114
of the youth leaders from
the State of Alabama up here.

16:25.288 --> 16:26.681
All right.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.770
Now let's stand
and clap for God!

16:28.944 --> 16:29.597
[audience cheering]
Come on!

16:29.771 --> 16:32.208
[upbeat music]

16:38.432 --> 16:41.913
[upbeat music continues]

16:42.088 --> 16:42.871
- Go!

16:48.790 --> 16:49.791
- Hey, rock and roll.

16:52.054 --> 16:53.969
You need to come to my
party this Saturday.

16:54.143 --> 16:56.145
- You're Dr. Blackburn's
daughter, are you?

16:58.713 --> 16:59.844
Rock and roll.

17:00.019 --> 17:00.758
Wow.

17:02.064 --> 17:03.805
That was a, that's
a gospel song.

17:03.979 --> 17:06.242
- I'm Angie, and
it's called a joke.

17:06.416 --> 17:08.679
It's a 4th of July
party. Just come.

17:08.853 --> 17:10.072
Your song was groovy.

17:10.246 --> 17:12.335
- Thank you.
- This Saturday at 12:00.

17:12.509 --> 17:14.424
Barbecue and everything.

17:15.991 --> 17:17.862
But no swimming trunks.
Swimming's of the devil.

17:21.257 --> 17:22.693
- [Samuel] It's
nice to meet you.

17:26.436 --> 17:28.003
- [Julie] Hi, Samuel

17:30.310 --> 17:31.180
- Julie.

17:31.354 --> 17:32.268
[Julie chuckles]

17:32.442 --> 17:33.965
Haven't seen you in a while.

17:34.140 --> 17:36.403
My momma used to listen
to the record y'all made

17:36.577 --> 17:39.058
with your daddy
when you were kids.

17:39.232 --> 17:39.928
- Oh.

17:40.102 --> 17:41.060
Well, thank you.

17:42.583 --> 17:44.585
- She said that y'all
are getting married.

17:46.239 --> 17:48.197
- Ah. You must be
making things up.

17:48.371 --> 17:50.721
- Actually, I, [sighs]
I did say that.

17:50.895 --> 17:53.202
- That's cool, I just, I
didn't give you a ring yet.

17:56.379 --> 17:57.424
- Uh, I...

17:57.598 --> 17:58.773
Sorry, I gotta, I gotta go.

17:58.947 --> 18:00.514
We gotta go. Come on, Ray.

18:00.688 --> 18:02.255
- Um, whoa, hey, uh, Angie,

18:02.429 --> 18:04.257
Angie Blackburn's having
a party this Saturday.

18:04.431 --> 18:05.780
- Well, I- I don't think
my daddy would let me go.

18:05.954 --> 18:08.217
He doesn't really let us, um-

18:08.391 --> 18:09.436
- What?

18:09.610 --> 18:10.089
Have fun?

18:11.960 --> 18:12.743
Please?

18:14.745 --> 18:16.834
Look, it's at noon, and I just
wanna keep talking to you,

18:17.008 --> 18:18.532
so I'll go if you're going.

18:24.799 --> 18:26.540
- He's waiting, but I'll try.

18:30.283 --> 18:31.458
Oh, wait, um...

18:34.156 --> 18:35.636
Here.

18:35.810 --> 18:38.639
This used to be mine, but
I want you to have it.

18:38.813 --> 18:40.249
[gentle music]

18:40.423 --> 18:42.077
You can hold onto it till
you give me that ring.

18:44.819 --> 18:48.301
[gentle music continues]

18:54.220 --> 18:57.440
[gentle music continues]

18:57.614 --> 19:00.139
[ominous music]

19:01.749 --> 19:04.273
[Julie giggles]

19:05.840 --> 19:10.497
[slap thwacks]
[Julie gasps]

19:14.762 --> 19:17.373
