1:00:39.810 --> 1:00:40.506
- Here.

1:00:40.680 --> 1:00:41.420
- No, keep it.

1:00:45.511 --> 1:00:46.251
- Well.

1:00:48.340 --> 1:00:49.689
Don't change too much.

1:00:52.300 --> 1:00:53.954
You're one of the
sweetest people I know.

1:00:56.391 --> 1:00:57.784
Next one's on me, Barry.

1:00:57.958 --> 1:00:59.220
- God. Get outta here.

1:01:04.704 --> 1:01:08.012
[brooding music continues]

1:01:10.275 --> 1:01:12.625
[Barry sighs]

1:01:19.066 --> 1:01:22.504
[brooding music continues]

1:01:25.420 --> 1:01:29.337
- [sighs] I'm
trying. I'm trying.

1:01:34.603 --> 1:01:37.824
[brooding music continues]

1:01:45.440 --> 1:01:48.008
[camera shutter clicking]

1:01:48.182 --> 1:01:49.357
Hey!

1:01:49.531 --> 1:01:53.057
[camera shutter clicks]

1:01:53.231 --> 1:01:55.276
Why are you following
me and taking pictures?

1:01:55.450 --> 1:01:56.234
What you trying to do, huh?

1:01:56.408 --> 1:01:57.888
- I got you now.

1:01:58.062 --> 1:02:00.281
Pictures of that
going up to your room, huh?

1:02:03.632 --> 1:02:05.809
[groans] Oh, and now the liquor.

1:02:07.288 --> 1:02:10.161
Now a Black burnout assaulting
an upstanding citizen.

1:02:11.815 --> 1:02:14.687
Samuel's going down.
You too, Barry.

1:02:14.861 --> 1:02:18.386
- Get your stuff and get
outta here, you redneck.

1:02:20.345 --> 1:02:21.041
Get outta here!

1:02:28.440 --> 1:02:33.140
[door creaking]
[ominous music]

1:02:38.667 --> 1:02:41.758
[ominous music continues]

1:02:46.980 --> 1:02:49.940
[telephone ringing]

1:02:51.855 --> 1:02:52.638
- Hello?

1:02:53.595 --> 1:02:54.422
- It's me, brother.

1:02:56.642 --> 1:02:57.425
- Barry.

1:02:58.426 --> 1:02:59.210
Barry, what is it?

1:03:03.692 --> 1:03:05.651
Oh, you know. Same old story.

1:03:08.436 --> 1:03:10.134
- Um, hey, hold on.

1:03:10.308 --> 1:03:12.658
Where are you? Where are you at?

1:03:12.832 --> 1:03:14.399
- That's a deep question.

1:03:20.535 --> 1:03:21.449
At the bottom of a well.

1:03:25.018 --> 1:03:27.804
[sobs] I can see the light, but

1:03:29.893 --> 1:03:31.677
I just can't reach it.

1:03:33.461 --> 1:03:34.767
It's too far away

1:03:40.077 --> 1:03:43.123
T.L. Whittmore had
a goon following me,

1:03:43.297 --> 1:03:44.124
taking pictures of me,

1:03:45.865 --> 1:03:48.476
drinking, and with a prostitute.

1:03:48.650 --> 1:03:51.044
But I ain't go through with it.

1:03:52.785 --> 1:03:53.786
I'm different now.

1:03:55.832 --> 1:03:58.269
But, uh,

1:03:58.443 --> 1:04:00.488
I messed it up for you.

1:04:00.662 --> 1:04:02.969
[ominous music continues]

1:04:03.143 --> 1:04:06.059
They said they're
gonna take your church.

1:04:06.233 --> 1:04:07.844
- That doesn't matter
right now, Barry.

1:04:09.323 --> 1:04:12.065
- When I get sad, I drink.

1:04:12.239 --> 1:04:15.634
[ominous music continues]

1:04:15.808 --> 1:04:17.810
I can't fix it, brother.

1:04:22.380 --> 1:04:23.511
I love you, brother.

1:04:27.211 --> 1:04:29.213
- I love you too,
Barry. God loves you.

1:04:29.387 --> 1:04:29.866
Um...

1:04:31.258 --> 1:04:34.044
[ominous music continues]

1:04:34.218 --> 1:04:35.872
Look, um, we're just
gonna get through this.

1:04:36.046 --> 1:04:37.612
I need you to tell me
where you are, Barry.

1:04:37.786 --> 1:04:40.006
You have to tell me, please.

1:04:40.180 --> 1:04:41.747
- I'm sorry. I let you down.

1:04:41.921 --> 1:04:44.489
- You didn't let me down, Barry.

1:04:46.230 --> 1:04:46.970
Barry.

1:04:49.189 --> 1:04:49.929
Barry?

1:04:51.452 --> 1:04:53.367
[gun cocking]

1:04:53.541 --> 1:04:54.325
Barry?

1:04:58.982 --> 1:05:01.419
[gunshot bangs]

1:05:01.593 --> 1:05:03.595
[sirens wailing]

1:05:03.769 --> 1:05:06.337
[brooding music]

1:05:10.602 --> 1:05:13.039
[sirens wailing]

1:05:20.438 --> 1:05:23.920
[brooding music continues]

1:05:25.530 --> 1:05:27.924
[somber music]

1:05:29.969 --> 1:05:32.798
[thunder rumbling]

1:05:39.326 --> 1:05:42.590
[somber music continues]

1:05:49.249 --> 1:05:52.513
[somber music continues]

1:05:55.560 --> 1:05:57.083
- [Samuel] Mr. Whittmore.

1:05:57.257 --> 1:05:58.824
I thought that might be
you when I saw that car.

1:05:58.998 --> 1:05:59.999
- [T.L.] Is that right?

1:06:00.173 --> 1:06:01.740
- Hey, you and those Cadillacs.

1:06:04.830 --> 1:06:06.310
- Is there some
place we can talk?

1:06:12.751 --> 1:06:13.970
We got a problem.

1:06:18.496 --> 1:06:21.716
[thunder rumbling]

1:06:21.890 --> 1:06:22.979
I've been watching you

1:06:24.806 --> 1:06:28.419
over the years since your
so-called conversion.

1:06:29.681 --> 1:06:30.682
- So-called?

1:06:30.856 --> 1:06:31.639
- Hmm.

1:06:33.467 --> 1:06:36.905
There ain't a thing sacred about
the way you do church, son.

1:06:37.080 --> 1:06:38.385
[thunder rumbling]

1:06:38.559 --> 1:06:40.257
Worldly music.

1:06:40.431 --> 1:06:41.388
Weirdos.

1:06:42.650 --> 1:06:44.000
It seems like you think,

1:06:44.174 --> 1:06:45.914
just 'cause you run
three services a Sunday,

1:06:46.089 --> 1:06:49.179
that somehow you're justified.

1:06:49.353 --> 1:06:51.137
- Everyone deserves
a second chance.

1:06:51.311 --> 1:06:52.660
- Shame Barry didn't get one.

1:06:54.967 --> 1:06:56.925
Drunk usher one day,
kills himself the next.

1:06:57.100 --> 1:06:58.449
- You don't get to bring him up.

1:06:58.623 --> 1:07:00.364
You don't know
anything about Barry.

1:07:00.538 --> 1:07:02.670
- I know you refuse to
preach sanctification.

1:07:04.324 --> 1:07:05.412
Hmm?

1:07:05.586 --> 1:07:07.545
[T.L. sniggers]

1:07:07.719 --> 1:07:10.374
Your daddy was a grace
man. Look at him now.

1:07:14.465 --> 1:07:16.989
- You want me to preach
that people lose the ability

1:07:17.163 --> 1:07:19.035
to make a mistake after
they come to the Lord?

1:07:19.209 --> 1:07:20.601
- It's mighty close
to the line, son.

1:07:20.775 --> 1:07:22.168
- Matter of fact,
it's over the lie.

1:07:22.342 --> 1:07:24.170
- Oh, you made up the line.

1:07:24.344 --> 1:07:25.737
You're gonna try and tell me
that, in 30 years of ministry,

1:07:25.911 --> 1:07:26.607
you've never made one mistake?

1:07:26.781 --> 1:07:27.695
- Not a one!

1:07:31.351 --> 1:07:32.091
Holiness.

1:07:33.223 --> 1:07:33.919
Look it up.

1:07:37.357 --> 1:07:38.054
- That's the problem.

1:07:42.232 --> 1:07:42.928
I have.

1:07:45.104 --> 1:07:46.540
- A sinner like you
wouldn't understand.

1:07:46.714 --> 1:07:49.282
[thunder rumbling]

1:07:51.589 --> 1:07:55.375
- "I was shown mercy so that
in me, the worst of sinners,

1:07:55.549 --> 1:07:58.248
Christ Jesus might display
his immense patience."

1:07:58.422 --> 1:08:01.338
- "And these shall go away
into everlasting punishment,

1:08:01.512 --> 1:08:04.645
but the righteous
into life eternal."

1:08:04.819 --> 1:08:07.431
- "He has not punished us as
we deserve for all our sins,

1:08:07.605 --> 1:08:09.650
for his mercy toward those
who fear and honor him

1:08:09.824 --> 1:08:11.609
is as great as the height of
the heavens above the earth."

1:08:11.783 --> 1:08:13.306
- "They that have done evil

1:08:13.480 --> 1:08:16.092
will come upon the
resurrection of damnation,

1:08:17.397 --> 1:08:19.312
for the wages of sin is death."

1:08:21.314 --> 1:08:22.228
- It's sad.

1:08:23.360 --> 1:08:26.058
You've clearly memorized it, but

1:08:28.365 --> 1:08:30.149
you, you don't understand it.

1:08:35.981 --> 1:08:36.982
- You wanna hit me, boy?

1:08:39.593 --> 1:08:41.421
Prove what I already
know about you.

1:08:41.595 --> 1:08:44.120
[thunder rumbling]

1:08:48.428 --> 1:08:49.255
You're out!

1:08:51.866 --> 1:08:54.347
I believe the Pope calls
it excommunicated. Hmm.

1:08:57.611 --> 1:08:59.787
No one from the GCO will
ever speak to you again.

1:09:03.095 --> 1:09:06.054
Brother Malachi will
move into the parsonage

1:09:06.229 --> 1:09:08.274
and take over this
Saturday, all right?

1:09:10.407 --> 1:09:11.582
You're finished.

1:09:11.756 --> 1:09:14.367
[brooding music]

1:09:15.803 --> 1:09:18.676
[thunder rumbling]

1:09:22.593 --> 1:09:23.681
- Barry's death is on you.

1:09:27.815 --> 1:09:28.947
- I wasn't his pastor.

1:09:31.950 --> 1:09:33.299
You were.

1:09:33.473 --> 1:09:37.477
[brooding music continues]

1:09:37.651 --> 1:09:40.176
[door slams]

1:09:47.705 --> 1:09:49.097
- Daddy will just
be a minute, okay?

1:09:49.272 --> 1:09:50.490
He's saying goodbye to Poppa.

1:09:50.664 --> 1:09:51.796
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay.

1:09:53.276 --> 1:09:55.191
- Hey, don't let
'em make you bitter.

1:09:57.149 --> 1:09:59.499
[melancholy music]

1:09:59.673 --> 1:10:00.413
- Yeah.

1:10:01.936 --> 1:10:02.937
- You can only love
the Lord as much

1:10:03.111 --> 1:10:04.374
as the person you love least.

1:10:06.506 --> 1:10:08.508
- Dad, they took our legacy.

1:10:08.682 --> 1:10:09.205
- Your legacy?

1:10:11.729 --> 1:10:12.730
Your legacy's right here.

1:10:14.949 --> 1:10:18.214
It's right out
there in that car.

1:10:18.388 --> 1:10:19.780
It's anywhere God leads you,

1:10:19.954 --> 1:10:21.565
as long as you keep
your heart right.

1:10:23.044 --> 1:10:23.828
- We're, uh,

1:10:25.308 --> 1:10:28.311
we're gonna go to Florida.

1:10:28.485 --> 1:10:30.748
We like it down there.
Disney World and everything.

1:10:30.922 --> 1:10:33.316
- Yeah. That'll be good.

1:10:33.490 --> 1:10:35.927
- So we'll just start over.

1:10:36.101 --> 1:10:39.670
[melancholy music continues]

1:10:42.499 --> 1:10:43.369
- Here's $5,000.

1:10:43.543 --> 1:10:45.241
- Dad.
- Nope. Take it.

1:10:45.415 --> 1:10:46.807
- Dad.

1:10:46.981 --> 1:10:47.634
It's just been waiting
on a rainy day.

1:10:47.808 --> 1:10:48.461
It's yours.

1:10:52.900 --> 1:10:53.684
- Dad.

1:10:54.902 --> 1:10:55.338
Thank you.

1:10:56.904 --> 1:10:57.818
Come with us.

1:10:57.992 --> 1:11:00.168
- Oh, I can't come with you.

1:11:00.343 --> 1:11:01.126
I belong here.

1:11:02.519 --> 1:11:04.695
Your mom and I built this place.

1:11:07.350 --> 1:11:08.133
It's your time.

1:11:09.569 --> 1:11:10.309
- I love you.

1:11:12.268 --> 1:11:13.486
- I love you too.

1:11:15.358 --> 1:11:19.057
[melancholy music continues]

1:11:24.323 --> 1:11:26.804
[upbeat music]

1:11:28.719 --> 1:11:32.679
♪ It's a sort of magic from
the way that you love me ♪

1:11:32.853 --> 1:11:36.814
♪ It's a sort of magic, hold
you steady down, steady down ♪

1:11:36.988 --> 1:11:40.644
♪ It's a sort of magic from
the way that you love me ♪

1:11:40.818 --> 1:11:45.475
♪ It's a sort of magic, hold
you steady down, steady down ♪

1:11:46.389 --> 1:11:50.218
♪ Steady down, steady down ♪

1:11:50.393 --> 1:11:53.526
♪ Steady down, steady down ♪

1:11:57.138 --> 1:11:58.444
[audience applauding]

1:11:58.618 --> 1:12:00.272
- Ah.

1:12:00.446 --> 1:12:02.666
Ladies and gentlemen, we're
gonna take a 15-minute break,

1:12:02.840 --> 1:12:04.842
and we'll be right back to play
some more of your requests.

1:12:05.016 --> 1:12:07.323
[upbeat music]

1:12:12.066 --> 1:12:14.765
- [Waitron] One water and
one cabernet. [laughs]

1:12:14.939 --> 1:12:16.462
- [Julie] Thanks.

1:12:16.636 --> 1:12:17.811
- [Waitron] Can I get
you anything else?

1:12:17.985 --> 1:12:19.465
- No, thank you.

1:12:19.639 --> 1:12:21.380
- [Waitron] All right.

1:12:24.122 --> 1:12:27.343
[upbeat music continues]

1:12:31.564 --> 1:12:32.565
- So what was that about?

1:12:34.872 --> 1:12:37.483
- Dom Rivera there
just offered us a job.

1:12:37.657 --> 1:12:38.397
- What?

1:12:39.311 --> 1:12:40.486
Who's Dom Rivera?

1:12:40.660 --> 1:12:42.227
Oh, he's a businessman.

1:12:42.401 --> 1:12:43.837
He wants to become the main
act at his new nightclub,

1:12:44.011 --> 1:12:47.232
but, ah, he wants a
one-year contract.

1:12:48.886 --> 1:12:52.280
- [chuckles] Oh, that's
good news, right?

1:12:52.455 --> 1:12:53.891
- You want me to take the job?

1:13:00.114 --> 1:13:02.247
I mean, I- I- I- I- I
thought this was temporary.

1:13:02.421 --> 1:13:03.901
W- we have to start the church

1:13:04.075 --> 1:13:05.293
to prove to all the T.L.
Whittmores of the world

1:13:05.468 --> 1:13:06.904
that our way works, too.

1:13:07.078 --> 1:13:08.775
- I'm sorry, Okay? I
just need a minute.

1:13:08.949 --> 1:13:09.689
- Hey!

1:13:10.777 --> 1:13:12.779
Julie.

1:13:12.953 --> 1:13:13.737
Julie!

1:13:18.394 --> 1:13:19.569
Hey, you are causing a scene.

1:13:20.787 --> 1:13:21.527
Julie.

1:13:24.138 --> 1:13:25.618
Julie, what's going on with you?

1:13:33.278 --> 1:13:35.846
[Julie sighs]

1:13:36.020 --> 1:13:38.370
- I saw my daddy at the
grocery store today.

1:13:38.544 --> 1:13:40.981
- Oh, baby, you know
that's not possible.

1:13:41.155 --> 1:13:42.418
- He was just standing there,

1:13:43.506 --> 1:13:44.942
[somber music]

1:13:45.116 --> 1:13:46.291
staring at me

1:13:49.729 --> 1:13:50.643
like a ghost.

1:13:53.603 --> 1:13:55.300
- Baby, there's no
such thing as ghosts.

1:13:57.302 --> 1:14:00.566
[somber music continues]

1:14:03.308 --> 1:14:05.615
Look, I'm fighting
for our dream.

1:14:06.746 --> 1:14:09.009
I still want our own church.

1:14:12.883 --> 1:14:14.450
- You...

1:14:14.624 --> 1:14:15.668
I don't know if I do.

1:14:17.583 --> 1:14:19.933
- Look, you might've
had too much wine.

1:14:20.107 --> 1:14:20.673
- Don't do that.

1:14:22.109 --> 1:14:23.676
Our life was stolen from us.

1:14:25.722 --> 1:14:27.854
Oh, but th- th-
th- this is easy.

1:14:28.028 --> 1:14:31.118
We're playing music, we get
paid, we sing, we go home.

1:14:31.292 --> 1:14:32.816
Repeat, do it again,
no one judging.

1:14:32.990 --> 1:14:34.470
- Well, maybe it is,

1:14:34.644 --> 1:14:36.341
but you knew who I was
when you married me.

1:14:36.515 --> 1:14:39.692
- I know, I did, I did. I
just didn't know who I was.

1:14:41.868 --> 1:14:43.174
Samuel, I...

1:14:43.348 --> 1:14:46.612
[somber music continues]

1:14:52.313 --> 1:14:55.491
[somber music continues]

1:14:57.405 --> 1:14:58.798
I was only five years old

1:14:58.972 --> 1:15:00.887
the first time that my
daddy crawled into my bed.

1:15:05.588 --> 1:15:06.327
And I...

1:15:13.204 --> 1:15:16.686
[somber music continues]

1:15:19.036 --> 1:15:20.298
So don't tell me

1:15:23.344 --> 1:15:25.564
that there's no such
thing as ghosts.

1:15:29.525 --> 1:15:32.745
[somber music continues]

1:15:37.707 --> 1:15:40.536
[birds twittering]

1:15:42.755 --> 1:15:44.975
[TV blaring]

1:15:52.373 --> 1:15:55.594
[TV blaring continues]

1:16:02.079 --> 1:16:04.081
[TV blaring continues]

1:16:04.255 --> 1:16:06.562
[gentle music]

1:16:12.045 --> 1:16:14.744
- [knocking] Julie?

1:16:19.226 --> 1:16:20.488
[knocking] Julie?

1:16:20.663 --> 1:16:23.361
[Julie sobbing]

1:16:23.535 --> 1:16:26.059
- Can you please shut the door?

1:16:26.233 --> 1:16:28.584
[somber music]

1:16:36.592 --> 1:16:38.898
- Baby, I'm worried about you.

1:16:40.683 --> 1:16:42.641
You've been in here a week,
and you haven't eaten.

1:16:46.123 --> 1:16:48.386
I d- I don't know what to do.

1:16:49.474 --> 1:16:50.431
- I need some time.

1:16:50.606 --> 1:16:51.389
I just

1:16:53.130 --> 1:16:54.827
can't get everything
out of my head.

1:16:57.047 --> 1:16:58.570
- Look, if you don't
talk to me, then-

1:16:58.744 --> 1:17:00.224
- Samuel, I need you
to just leave me alone.

1:17:00.398 --> 1:17:03.749
- Well, can you at least
just tell me what I can do?

1:17:03.923 --> 1:17:07.057
[somber music continues]

1:17:09.537 --> 1:17:11.278
- Can you rewrite history?

1:17:16.327 --> 1:17:19.983
Can you undo what
my daddy did to me?

1:17:20.157 --> 1:17:21.854
Or can you give us
our old life back?

1:17:27.730 --> 1:17:30.994
[somber music continues]

1:17:34.258 --> 1:17:35.041
- No.

1:17:40.351 --> 1:17:44.137
[somber music continues]

1:17:44.311 --> 1:17:45.617
I can love you.

1:17:48.664 --> 1:17:49.621
I can pray for you.

1:17:54.365 --> 1:17:55.888
- Then just do that.

1:17:57.716 --> 1:18:00.893
[somber music continues]

1:18:04.941 --> 1:18:07.813
[telephone ringing]

1:18:15.342 --> 1:18:16.779
- Hello?

1:18:16.953 --> 1:18:18.171
- [Caller] Could I speak
with Samuel, please?

1:18:18.345 --> 1:18:19.912
- Yeah, this is him.

1:18:20.086 --> 1:18:23.046
- [Dr. Emmett] This is Dr.
Emmett from the hospital.

1:18:23.220 --> 1:18:24.700
I served in the war
with your father.

1:18:26.963 --> 1:18:30.401
Son, your daddy
had a heart attack.

1:18:30.575 --> 1:18:33.186
I'm sorry to tell you,
he didn't make it.

1:18:33.360 --> 1:18:34.840
- Uh-
- I'm sorry, son.

1:18:36.233 --> 1:18:37.582
He was a good man.

1:18:40.193 --> 1:18:43.370
[somber music continues]

1:18:49.246 --> 1:18:52.510
[somber music continues]

1:18:58.516 --> 1:19:01.737
[somber music continues]

1:19:07.525 --> 1:19:10.963
[somber music continues]

1:19:13.966 --> 1:19:16.795
[birds twittering]

1:19:19.493 --> 1:19:21.931
[somber music]

1:19:29.721 --> 1:19:31.679
- "Often I dream
of your kindness.

1:19:31.854 --> 1:19:33.159
Daily I dream of your touch.

1:19:34.639 --> 1:19:36.206
Oceans won't quell my desire.

1:19:36.380 --> 1:19:38.121
My darling, I miss you so much."

1:19:41.994 --> 1:19:43.648
Dad, you were a poet?

1:19:45.432 --> 1:19:48.653
[somber music continues]

1:19:54.050 --> 1:19:57.967
[somber music continues]

1:19:58.141 --> 1:19:59.533
- [Joe] Today my
boy got in trouble.

1:19:59.707 --> 1:20:01.144
I got a call this morning,

1:20:01.318 --> 1:20:02.406
not from the police
department in Weems,

1:20:02.580 --> 1:20:03.755
where he was arrested,

1:20:04.669 --> 1:20:06.062
but from T.L. Whittmore.

1:20:07.324 --> 1:20:09.021
He told me my son was
in a bit of trouble,

1:20:09.195 --> 1:20:12.372
and he wanted me to meet him
in a coffee shop in Weems.

1:20:12.546 --> 1:20:13.547
I wanted to help my son.

1:20:14.679 --> 1:20:15.593
He wanted to cut a deal.

1:20:15.767 --> 1:20:18.204
[Samuel gasps]

1:20:19.336 --> 1:20:22.600
[somber music continues]

1:20:26.691 --> 1:20:29.694
[suspenseful music]

1:20:36.570 --> 1:20:40.052
[suspenseful music continues]

1:20:46.798 --> 1:20:50.236
[suspenseful music continues]

1:20:52.021 --> 1:20:54.762
- Read September 29th,
1969. You're right.

1:20:54.937 --> 1:20:56.852
I can't rewrite history,
but I can change the future.

1:20:57.026 --> 1:20:59.202
- Wait. Samuel, please,
where are you going?

1:21:01.857 --> 1:21:05.556
[suspenseful music continues]

1:21:05.730 --> 1:21:08.733
[engine starting]
Sammy!

1:21:11.649 --> 1:21:12.432
Sam!

1:21:14.565 --> 1:21:18.047
[suspenseful music continues]

1:21:21.789 --> 1:21:25.271
[suspenseful music continues]

1:21:31.625 --> 1:21:35.107
[suspenseful music continues]

1:21:41.635 --> 1:21:45.117
[suspenseful music continues]

1:21:51.776 --> 1:21:55.214
[suspenseful music continues]

1:22:00.872 --> 1:22:04.049
- I'm coming. [coughs]

1:22:04.223 --> 1:22:05.877
Lord Almighty, who...

1:22:07.661 --> 1:22:08.445
Samuel.

1:22:12.014 --> 1:22:14.842
- September 29th,

1:22:15.017 --> 1:22:15.800
1969.

1:22:17.845 --> 1:22:19.673
You made a deal with my dad.

1:22:24.113 --> 1:22:26.289
Now you tell me what happened.
I just wanna hear you say it.

1:22:32.034 --> 1:22:32.817
Say it!

1:22:35.820 --> 1:22:37.126
- I told your daddy

1:22:38.997 --> 1:22:40.825
that if he walked
away from the GCO,

1:22:40.999 --> 1:22:42.479
I'd have your charges dropped.

1:22:44.046 --> 1:22:45.047
Judge in Weems is
my brother-in-law.

1:22:46.831 --> 1:22:47.963
- Whats wrong with you?

1:22:51.488 --> 1:22:53.533
You took the one
thing from my father

1:22:55.057 --> 1:22:57.276
that he loved more than
anything in the world.

1:22:57.450 --> 1:22:58.147
- No.

1:22:59.626 --> 1:23:00.410
You got that wrong.

1:23:03.979 --> 1:23:05.067
- Is that right?

1:23:06.503 --> 1:23:07.286
- Yeah.

1:23:08.592 --> 1:23:10.289
He loved you more.

1:23:10.463 --> 1:23:12.944
[gentle music]

1:23:16.469 --> 1:23:17.209
Oh, uh...

1:23:18.471 --> 1:23:19.733
[gentle music continues]

1:23:19.907 --> 1:23:21.518
- Poppa, who is this?

1:23:23.563 --> 1:23:27.089
- Um, hey, I'm just here to
talk to your grandpa for a,

1:23:27.263 --> 1:23:28.003
for a minute.

1:23:31.049 --> 1:23:31.832
- Yeah, run on.

1:23:32.877 --> 1:23:36.141
[gentle music continues]

1:23:36.315 --> 1:23:37.664
Go on back inside.

1:23:39.362 --> 1:23:43.583
[clears throat]
He's my grandson.

1:23:43.757 --> 1:23:47.413
After Babsie died, I
hadn't been doing so well.

1:23:48.849 --> 1:23:51.026
My daughter's been
helping take care of me.

1:23:52.331 --> 1:23:53.593
I got a few months, I guess.

1:23:55.247 --> 1:23:58.381
I'm gonna pay for
my debts, Samuel.

1:23:58.555 --> 1:24:00.035
[somber music]

1:24:00.209 --> 1:24:00.992
I will.

1:24:01.775 --> 1:24:03.560
I already am.

1:24:03.734 --> 1:24:04.778
I don't even...

1:24:06.258 --> 1:24:07.999
I don't, I don't
deserve forgiveness.

1:24:10.523 --> 1:24:12.090
I know that.

1:24:12.264 --> 1:24:15.746
[somber music continues]

1:24:15.920 --> 1:24:18.227
- You never even asked for it.

1:24:21.621 --> 1:24:24.276
[Samuel sighs]

1:24:26.148 --> 1:24:29.412
[somber music continues]

1:24:33.198 --> 1:24:34.721
Look, no one
deserves forgiveness.

1:24:39.639 --> 1:24:42.294
It's just something we
receive, like a gift.

1:24:48.170 --> 1:24:49.432
T.L., I've been there.

1:24:49.606 --> 1:24:52.652
- [scoffs] No.

1:24:52.826 --> 1:24:57.004
No, I'm afraid not, son.
You haven't been here.

1:24:57.179 --> 1:24:58.745
- Look, God forgave
me at my lowest.

1:25:01.531 --> 1:25:03.010
My bitterness toward
you is no better

1:25:03.185 --> 1:25:05.230
than the things you did to me.

1:25:06.405 --> 1:25:08.842
[gentle music]

1:25:15.806 --> 1:25:16.981
I forgive you.

1:25:18.635 --> 1:25:21.899
[gentle music continues]

1:25:27.296 --> 1:25:29.820
- I don't know what to say.

1:25:29.994 --> 1:25:32.779
[gentle music continues]

1:25:32.953 --> 1:25:35.739
[Samuel sniggers]

1:25:37.871 --> 1:25:40.265
- Well, that's a first.

1:25:40.439 --> 1:25:44.226
[gentle music continues]

1:25:44.400 --> 1:25:46.576
- Yeah, yeah, I reckon it is.

1:25:48.665 --> 1:25:51.885
[gentle music continues]

1:25:59.241 --> 1:26:02.505
[gentle music continues]

1:26:04.681 --> 1:26:08.163
- [Samuel] [knocking] Julie?

1:26:08.337 --> 1:26:10.817
[somber music]

1:26:17.998 --> 1:26:21.437
[somber music continues]

1:26:21.611 --> 1:26:22.612
When I met you,

1:26:25.092 --> 1:26:27.617
you shone like a thousand stars.

1:26:29.140 --> 1:26:31.882
[somber music continues]

1:26:32.056 --> 1:26:32.839
But

1:26:37.017 --> 1:26:40.282
I never knew how much
you've been hurt.

1:26:40.456 --> 1:26:43.633
[somber music continues]

1:26:46.113 --> 1:26:49.943
I'm not gonna like you get
sucked under that current.

1:26:50.117 --> 1:26:51.510
I'm holding onto you.

1:26:53.512 --> 1:26:54.252
If you go,

1:26:55.297 --> 1:26:56.472
I go.

1:26:56.646 --> 1:26:59.866
[somber music continues]

1:27:02.913 --> 1:27:04.436
I don't have a dream
without you in it.

1:27:07.091 --> 1:27:07.874
So I,

1:27:09.572 --> 1:27:12.227
I did take the, the job
at the club, and, um,

1:27:16.622 --> 1:27:17.101
I also took a, took a side
job working on the railroad

1:27:19.146 --> 1:27:21.932
with Reyna's brother
to pay off our debt.

1:27:22.106 --> 1:27:25.065
[somber music continues]

1:27:25.240 --> 1:27:26.763
Just know I'm here for you.

1:27:28.852 --> 1:27:32.377
And I should've what
you were going through.

1:27:33.944 --> 1:27:37.382
[somber music continues]

1:27:37.556 --> 1:27:38.296
I'm sorry.

1:27:44.346 --> 1:27:46.261
I'm still praying for you.

1:27:50.656 --> 1:27:51.962
I love you.

1:27:52.136 --> 1:27:55.357
[somber music continues]

1:28:01.232 --> 1:28:03.800
[Julie sobbing]

1:28:06.803 --> 1:28:10.067
[somber music continues]

1:28:16.378 --> 1:28:19.598
[somber music continues]

1:28:24.342 --> 1:28:26.736
- [Foreman] All right, guys.
We're gonna take a long break.

1:28:26.910 --> 1:28:29.304
[gentle music]

1:28:31.871 --> 1:28:32.698
45 minutes.

1:28:36.180 --> 1:28:39.357
[gentle music continues]

1:28:42.491 --> 1:28:44.884
- "For all the land
which thou seest,

1:28:45.058 --> 1:28:48.932
to thee will I give it,
and to thy seed forever."

1:28:50.150 --> 1:28:53.371
[gentle music continues]

1:28:57.419 --> 1:29:00.639
[gentle music continues]

1:29:05.818 --> 1:29:07.820
Everything I see, huh?

1:29:07.994 --> 1:29:09.692
Hey, boss!

1:29:09.866 --> 1:29:12.390
- Allen, can't you
see I'm resting?

1:29:12.564 --> 1:29:14.131
- Yeah, sorry, uh...

1:29:16.176 --> 1:29:17.569
Hey, what if I told
you that the Lord said

1:29:17.743 --> 1:29:19.745
he was gonna gimme
everything I see right now?

1:29:22.879 --> 1:29:25.272
- Well, I say, as long as
you ain't looking at me,

1:29:25.447 --> 1:29:28.232
you can have it.

1:29:28.406 --> 1:29:29.451
- Where are we?

1:29:31.104 --> 1:29:32.584
- [Foreman] St. Cloud.

1:29:33.846 --> 1:29:35.282
- St. Cloud.

1:29:35.457 --> 1:29:36.936
- Yeah.

1:29:37.110 --> 1:29:38.373
And you can have it.

1:29:44.640 --> 1:29:47.817
♪ Sinking in the deep ♪

1:29:47.991 --> 1:29:52.691
♪ Standing on a ledge ♪

1:29:53.692 --> 1:29:58.393
♪ But you ♪

1:29:59.437 --> 1:30:01.483
♪ You still love me ♪

1:30:01.657 --> 1:30:02.614
- It's beautiful.

1:30:04.399 --> 1:30:05.617
- Uh, you scared me.

1:30:06.923 --> 1:30:08.228
- Sorry.

1:30:08.403 --> 1:30:09.360
- It's okay. I
shoulda come to bed.

1:30:11.231 --> 1:30:13.233
- No, it's okay. You
worked really hard.

1:30:15.453 --> 1:30:17.281
- Yeah, it's, it's
harder than I thought.

1:30:25.463 --> 1:30:27.073
- You know, my daddy,

1:30:30.729 --> 1:30:32.601
my daddy said that no
one would ever love me

1:30:32.775 --> 1:30:34.472
once they found out
what he'd done to me.

1:30:36.431 --> 1:30:38.824
And I wanted to tell you, but

1:30:40.522 --> 1:30:43.089
I loved you and I got scared.

1:30:47.746 --> 1:30:49.052
But you protected me.

1:30:51.315 --> 1:30:52.447
You believed in me.

1:31:01.891 --> 1:31:02.979
I, uh...

1:31:06.199 --> 1:31:09.899
I read your daddy's journals.
[gentle music]

1:31:10.073 --> 1:31:12.467
He called your destiny
his Promised Land.

1:31:14.556 --> 1:31:16.688
Okay, he knew what he was
doing when he walked away.

1:31:20.823 --> 1:31:23.521
[sighs] I got lost
somewhere along the way.

1:31:26.785 --> 1:31:28.134
But you kept loving me.

1:31:30.528 --> 1:31:31.703
And you said you prayed for me.

1:31:34.619 --> 1:31:36.621
And this morning
I woke up and I,

1:31:39.537 --> 1:31:42.540
[sighs] I felt hope.

1:31:44.455 --> 1:31:46.022
And I prayed for us.

1:31:50.287 --> 1:31:51.157
Samuel Allen,

1:31:53.769 --> 1:31:55.684
It is time for me
to believe in you.

1:31:58.121 --> 1:32:00.602
[rousing music]

1:32:06.564 --> 1:32:09.611
- I don't wanna
do it without you.

1:32:09.785 --> 1:32:13.136
[rousing music continues]

1:32:14.398 --> 1:32:15.530
- You won't have to.

1:32:17.183 --> 1:32:20.535
[rousing music continues]

1:32:26.453 --> 1:32:29.544
[rousing music continues]

1:32:36.289 --> 1:32:39.597
[rousing music continues]

1:32:41.556 --> 1:32:44.428
[birds twittering]

1:32:48.214 --> 1:32:51.130
- Hey, Julie, did you get my
guitar picks off the table?

1:32:51.304 --> 1:32:51.870
- Yeah, I got 'em.

1:32:53.698 --> 1:32:54.525
- [Samuel] All right,
sorry, I'm just, um,

1:32:54.699 --> 1:32:55.657
I'm a little nervous.

1:32:55.831 --> 1:32:57.354
- Dad, are, are we moving?

1:32:57.528 --> 1:33:00.705
- Uh, well, son, we only
got invited to minister.

1:33:00.879 --> 1:33:02.620
- If we move, can I
get a bigger room?

1:33:02.794 --> 1:33:04.361
- Hey, I want a bigger room too!

1:33:04.535 --> 1:33:07.494
- Kids, I don't know
that we're moving.

1:33:07.669 --> 1:33:09.409
- Aw!

1:33:09.584 --> 1:33:10.976
- What exactly did the man say?

1:33:12.761 --> 1:33:14.589
- He's part of the
advisory board.

1:33:14.763 --> 1:33:16.373
Their pastor left, and
they asked us to fill in

1:33:16.547 --> 1:33:18.244
till decisions are
made on a new pastor.

1:33:19.768 --> 1:33:20.725
- A pastor like you.

1:33:21.987 --> 1:33:25.469
- We're the Allen
family, and, uh,

1:33:25.643 --> 1:33:26.905
we're gonna sing a song for you.

1:33:29.081 --> 1:33:31.693
[birds twittering]

1:33:37.524 --> 1:33:39.004
My, my friend wrote this song.

1:33:44.053 --> 1:33:48.187
Uh, th- this wasn't planned,
but I'm gonna sing it.

1:33:52.235 --> 1:33:54.629
[bright music]

1:34:01.331 --> 1:34:04.508
[bright music continues]

1:34:05.727 --> 1:34:08.425
♪ I was tired ♪

1:34:08.599 --> 1:34:11.428
♪ I was cold ♪

1:34:11.602 --> 1:34:13.125
♪ I was burned ♪

1:34:13.299 --> 1:34:16.302
♪ I was alone ♪

1:34:16.476 --> 1:34:19.392
♪ Falling from the skies ♪

1:34:19.566 --> 1:34:22.308
♪ Hanging by a thread ♪

1:34:22.482 --> 1:34:25.224
♪ Sinking in the deep ♪

1:34:25.398 --> 1:34:30.099
♪ Standing on a ledge ♪

1:34:31.361 --> 1:34:36.018
♪ But you ♪

1:34:37.062 --> 1:34:41.284
♪ You still love me ♪

1:34:42.415 --> 1:34:46.332
♪ I'm thankful that you ♪

1:34:48.334 --> 1:34:53.035
♪ You still love me ♪

1:34:55.037 --> 1:34:58.127
♪ Now I'm flying high,
I'm glory bound ♪

1:34:58.301 --> 1:35:01.130
♪ I see the light,
I hear the sound ♪

1:35:01.304 --> 1:35:05.917
♪ The heavenly host from above ♪

1:35:07.179 --> 1:35:10.269
♪ A lost cause now is found ♪

1:35:10.443 --> 1:35:13.359
♪ A broken man wears the crown ♪

1:35:13.533 --> 1:35:18.234
♪ All because of your love ♪

1:35:21.367 --> 1:35:24.066
♪ You still love me ♪

1:35:31.421 --> 1:35:36.121
♪ Never gave up on me ♪

1:35:38.384 --> 1:35:43.085
♪ That's why I'm
so thankful, Lord ♪

1:35:45.478 --> 1:35:48.351
♪ You still loved me ♪

1:35:52.485 --> 1:35:55.750
[bright music continues]

1:36:00.015 --> 1:36:03.366
[congregation applauding]

1:36:09.633 --> 1:36:12.201
- Wow! [laughs]

1:36:12.375 --> 1:36:14.769
I have never heard music that
good in church before, ever.

1:36:17.032 --> 1:36:21.688
Our guests today have
come highly recommended.

1:36:23.168 --> 1:36:25.083
Obviously they are
incredible musicians,

1:36:25.257 --> 1:36:26.998
but they can preach, too.

1:36:28.434 --> 1:36:30.523
Please welcome
Pastor Samuel Allen.

1:36:30.697 --> 1:36:31.655
[congregation applauding]

1:36:31.829 --> 1:36:33.962
- Thank you so much. Thank you.

1:36:35.659 --> 1:36:37.922
Well, thank you.

1:36:38.096 --> 1:36:38.923
Thank you.

1:36:39.097 --> 1:36:39.837
You have

1:36:41.099 --> 1:36:42.579
no idea what an honor it is

1:36:42.753 --> 1:36:44.015
for us to be here
with you today.

1:36:45.364 --> 1:36:46.452
My wife,

1:36:46.626 --> 1:36:47.410
Julie,

1:36:48.454 --> 1:36:50.630
my kids, Jesse, Mia,

1:36:50.805 --> 1:36:52.241
We appreciate you having us.

1:36:54.156 --> 1:36:56.114
I just, I wanna
tell you something.

1:37:00.945 --> 1:37:04.340
You may have been
pushed around, beat up,

1:37:05.471 --> 1:37:06.342
run over,

1:37:07.299 --> 1:37:08.648
cheated on.

1:37:08.823 --> 1:37:10.389
- [Congregant] Amen.

1:37:10.563 --> 1:37:14.002
- Maybe you've done those
things to someone else.

1:37:14.176 --> 1:37:18.006
I'm just here to say that
there is always hope.

1:37:20.356 --> 1:37:22.010
And I'm not, I'm not
sure what your story is,

1:37:22.184 --> 1:37:25.143
but today I am here
to say that you never

1:37:25.317 --> 1:37:27.798
give up on the dream
that God has given you.

1:37:30.105 --> 1:37:30.845
Trust in him.

1:37:34.805 --> 1:37:37.025
Could y'all look at your,
look at your neighbor?

1:37:38.200 --> 1:37:41.029
Yeah, look at your
neighbor, and just say,

1:37:42.639 --> 1:37:44.032
"It's time to dream again."

1:37:45.294 --> 1:37:48.645
[congregation chattering]

1:37:49.733 --> 1:37:50.865
God bless you.
- Thank you.

1:37:51.039 --> 1:37:51.866
- [Samuel] Thank you.

1:37:52.040 --> 1:37:53.302
- [Julie] God bless.

1:37:53.476 --> 1:37:55.043
- Thank you.
- Thanks for coming.

1:37:55.217 --> 1:37:57.872
- [Samuel] Yeah, thank
you so much. God bless.

1:37:58.046 --> 1:37:59.395
- Thank you. Thank you again.
- I'm so proud of you.

1:37:59.569 --> 1:38:01.266
- Thank you. Thanks.

1:38:07.664 --> 1:38:08.447
Thank you.

1:38:09.709 --> 1:38:10.493
God bless you.

1:38:12.364 --> 1:38:16.107
- Well, Pastor Samuel, it has
been very nice to meet you.

1:38:16.281 --> 1:38:18.980
I'm sold. You have
an incredible family.

1:38:19.154 --> 1:38:21.243
Everyone here
obviously loves you.

1:38:21.417 --> 1:38:23.898
You are gonna build
a great church here.

1:38:26.944 --> 1:38:29.033
- W- w- what do,
what do you mean?

1:38:29.207 --> 1:38:30.817
- When the pastor
of this church left,

1:38:30.992 --> 1:38:34.038
it was legally turned over
to our advisory board,

1:38:34.212 --> 1:38:35.822
and someone of great influence,

1:38:35.997 --> 1:38:38.651
who wished to remain unnamed,

1:38:38.825 --> 1:38:40.610
paid the mortgage
off on this place

1:38:40.784 --> 1:38:45.354
with the stipulation that you
must become our new pastor.

1:38:46.572 --> 1:38:48.966
[gentle music]

1:38:49.140 --> 1:38:50.098
That's how we found you.

1:38:53.101 --> 1:38:55.712
Somebody thinks
very highly of you,

1:38:55.886 --> 1:38:56.843
so I'm gonna be here at 9:00 AM

1:38:57.018 --> 1:38:58.367
to turn over all the paperwork.

1:38:59.629 --> 1:39:00.108
If you want it,

1:39:02.458 --> 1:39:03.589
this place is yours.

1:39:04.895 --> 1:39:06.157
- I can't believe it.

1:39:08.855 --> 1:39:11.206
Um, I mean yes. Yes, of course.

1:39:11.380 --> 1:39:12.685
I mean, of course we want it,

1:39:12.859 --> 1:39:14.035
more than anything in the world.

1:39:15.819 --> 1:39:18.909
- You just preached a
wonderful sermon on dreams.

1:39:19.083 --> 1:39:20.302
I don't think you should
be surprised by this,

